rit"><div style=3D"font-size:inherit">
<p>Below is a complete 7-week course (10 hrs/week) designed to get students=
 from zero to research-grade, parameterized VR rooms with AI assistance. It=
 emphasizes controlled manipulation of variables (your CNfA priority), not =
traditional 3D craft.</p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h1>COURSE:&nbsp;</h1><h1>AI-Driven VR Stimulus Design for Cognitive=
 Science</h1><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Duration: 7 weeks</p>
<p>Workload: 10 hrs/week (=E2=89=8870 hrs total)</p>
<p>Outcome: Students build fully parameterized VR environments suitable for=
 experiments</p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h1>STRUCTURE OVERVIEW</h1><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Each week includes:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Objectives</p>
</li><li>
<p>Time allocation (10 hrs)</p>
</li><li>
<p>Deliverables</p>
</li><li>
<p>Assignments</p>
</li><li>
<p>AI prompts (ready to use)</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h1>WEEK 1 =E2=80=94 Foundations: Scene + Variables</h1><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Objectives</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Understand scene graph + parameters</p>
</li><li>
<p>Build first VR room</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Time Breakdown (10 hrs)</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>2h lecture: scene structure + experimental thinking</p>
</li><li>
<p>3h guided Unity work</p>
</li><li>
<p>5h independent build</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Tools</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Unity</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Assignment</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Build a basic room:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Floor, 4 walls, ceiling</p>
</li><li>
<p>1 light source</p>
</li><li>
<p>2 materials (e.g., wood vs concrete)</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Deliver:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Screenshot + short description</p>
</li><li>
<p>List of variables you could manipulate</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>AI Prompts</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Use inside ChatGPT / Claude:</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Prompt 1 =E2=80=94 Unity setup</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Explain step-by-step how to create a simple room in Unity using primitives.
Include exact menu paths and naming conventions.</code></pre>
<p>Prompt 2 =E2=80=94 Experimental thinking</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Given a simple room, list 10 variables that could influence perception=20
(e.g., stress, comfort, focus). Define each precisely.</code></pre>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h1>WEEK 2 =E2=80=94 Parameterization (CRITICAL WEEK)</h1><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Objectives</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Turn static room into controllable system</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Time</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>3h lecture/demo (variables + sliders)</p>
</li><li>
<p>7h implementation</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Assignment</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Add 5 adjustable parameters:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Room width</p>
</li><li>
<p>Ceiling height</p>
</li><li>
<p>Light intensity</p>
</li><li>
<p>Wall color</p>
</li><li>
<p>Object count</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Use:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>UI sliders OR inspector variables</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Deliver:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Demo video</p>
</li><li>
<p>Parameter list with ranges</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>AI Prompts</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Prompt =E2=80=94 Unity scripting</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Write a Unity C# script that allows real-time control of:
- room width
- ceiling height
- light intensity

Use sliders and explain where to attach the script.</code></pre>
<p>Prompt =E2=80=94 variable design</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Define good experimental ranges for:
- light intensity
- room size
- ceiling height

Avoid unrealistic values.</code></pre>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h1>WEEK 3 =E2=80=94 Materials, Textures, Lighting</h1><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Objectives</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Systematically manipulate perceptual properties</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Tools</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Substance 3D Sampler</p>
</li><li>
<p>Stable Diffusion</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Assignment</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Create 3 material conditions:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Natural (wood, warm tones)</p>
</li><li>
<p>Industrial (concrete, metal)</p>
</li><li>
<p>Soft (fabric, muted)</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Add:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>3 lighting conditions (cool / neutral / warm)</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Deliver</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Matrix of 9 conditions (3=C3=973)</p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>AI Prompts</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Prompt =E2=80=94 texture generation</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Generate prompts for creating seamless textures:
- wood
- concrete
- soft fabric

Include PBR map requirements.</code></pre>
<p>Prompt =E2=80=94 lighting</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Explain how to simulate warm vs cool lighting in Unity.
Include color temperature ranges in Kelvin.</code></pre>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h1>WEEK 4 =E2=80=94 AI Asset Generation + Layout</h1><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Objectives</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Rapidly populate environments</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Tools</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Meshy</p>
</li><li>
<p>Luma AI Genie</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Assignment</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Create 3 room layouts:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Sparse</p>
</li><li>
<p>Moderate</p>
</li><li>
<p>Cluttered</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Use AI-generated objects.</p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Deliver</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>3 scenes</p>
</li><li>
<p>Object count + density measure</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>AI Prompts</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Prompt =E2=80=94 asset generation</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Generate 10 text prompts for AI 3D models suitable for:
- a cozy room
- a minimalist office
- a cluttered workspace</code></pre>
<p>Prompt =E2=80=94 clutter metric</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Define a quantitative metric for visual clutter in a room.
Include at least 3 measurable components.</code></pre>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h1>WEEK 5 =E2=80=94 Windows, Space, Geometry</h1><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p></p><h2>Objectives</h2><p></p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Manipulate architectural structure</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Assignment</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Add parameters for:</p>
<p></p><ul><li>
<p>Window size</p>
</li><li>
<p>Window position</p>
</li><li>
<p>Ceiling shape (flat vs vaulted)</p>
</li><li>
<p>Room proportions</p>
</li></ul><p></p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>Deliver</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>At least 4 spatial conditions</p>
<p></p><hr><p></p>
<p></p><h2>AI Prompts</h2><p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Prompt =E2=80=94 geometry</p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
Explain how to programmatically change room proportions in Unity=20
