<p></p><h2>PROJECT_CONSTITUTION.md</h2><p></p>
<pre style=3D"font-family:monospace"><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">=
# Project Constitution

## Mission
Teach students to build parameterized VR environments that function as expe=
rimental stimuli.

## What the course is
- a methods course
- a rapid prototyping course
- a stimulus-design course for cognitive science

## What the course is not
- not a game-design course
- not an art course
- not a high-fidelity rendering course
- not a traditional 3D modeling course

## Non-negotiable principles
1. Every meaningful manipulation must be parameterized.
2. Variables should be as orthogonal as feasible.
3. Experimental control outranks polish.
4. Students must learn to define ranges, not merely make scenes.
5. Fast authoring tools are preferred over artisanal workflows.
6. AI is used to accelerate production, not to replace design judgment.
7. Final projects must be reproducible by another person.

## Core variables
- geometry
- materials
- lighting
- windows
- clutter
- sound

## Deliverable standard
A collaborator should be able to open the repo, understand the goals, and c=
ontinue the work without asking what the project is for.</code></pre>
